    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Static Roof Vents</title>
        <para>The CE 200 and CE 300 are equipped with static roof vents located along the upper center of the bus roof
            line.
        </para>
        <figure id="f47004132" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47004132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                     scalefitheight="208px"/>
            <caption>Figure 132. Static Roof Vent</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BUS ROOF PANEL OVERLAP</callout1>
                <callout1>2. STATIC ROOF VENT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. STATIC ROOF VENT MOUNTING RIVETS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>To remove the static air vent, if damaged:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center punch all rivets in preparation for removal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an 1/4" diameter replacement rivet of suitable length. Use a rivet gun of industrial
                quality to properly set rivets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a 17/64" diameter drill bit and a heavy duty reversible drill.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drill through rivet head until rivet sleeve separates from the rivet head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the static vent.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the area around the vent of sealant or gasket material.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
